4575.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
4575.description: When Toph discovers a quick way to make cash, Katara disapproves, and the rift between them has disastrous consequences.

4576.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
4576.description: In a Halloween installment, the gang looks into strange disappearances in a spooky town. There, an old lady named Hama teaches Katara some secret Waterbending techniques.

4577.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4577.description: SpongeBob must figure out how to do his job after accidentally shrinking himself. // Squidward invents a new sport to get back at SpongeBob and Patrick for annoying him.

4578.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4578.description: When SpongeBob mistakes an escaped convict for his driving instructor, it's the new teacher who learns a lesson. // When Krabs sends him searching for a missing toy, SpongeBob finds himself lost... in the lost & found!

4579.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
4579.description: A fungus mutant spreading through the sewers causes the Turtles and April to experience their worst fears as Leonardo must face his greatest fear- losing his team.

4580.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
4580.description: When Donnie upgrades Metalhead's artificial intelligence, he must decide if he can trust a sentient Metalhead or if he has created a new foe.

4581.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4581.description: To impress his fan club, Po releases the Mongolian Fist Demon. Now he has to figure out how to defeat the Demon and save the village and his fans!

4582.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4582.description: Po disobeys Shifu's orders and looks into the Mystical Mirror of Yin and Yang, creating two versions of himself: one good and one evil!

4583.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4583.description: The whole gang heads on a treasure hunt with the Rat King close on their tales trying to get to the treasure before they do.

4584.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4584.description: The penguins accidentally launch Leonard the Koala out of the zoo and into midtown Manhattan. // When all the little mammals in the zoo start to disappear the penguins suspect the new boa constrictor, Salvio, who just moved in to the Central Park Zoo.

4585.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4585.description: The gang heads to a food convention, but things go awry when they become stranded in the woods. // SpongeBob accidentally fibs to his pen pal, but when his friend comes to visit, he must keep the ruse going!

4586.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4586.description: When SpongeBob hides the secret formula in his home, it’s up to Gary to protect it from Plankton. // When a freak accident causes everyone in town to become as stupid as Patrick, Sandy must save the day.

4587.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4587.description: When a storm sweeps the Krusty Krab away, its crew and customers will need a crazed Krabs to lead them back home. // Patrick’s last baby tooth needs to come out, but he’s afraid to let it go.

4588.title: Nella The Princess Knight
4588.description: When Sir Coach embarks on a dangerous quest, Nella tags along and realizes she still has a lot to learn. // Nella helps Smelgly the dragon fulfill her dream of joining the Knight Brigade.

4589.title: Nella The Princess Knight
4589.description: Trinket is desperate to keep things perfect for Royal Family Picture Day. // Nella and Norma's 'Best Sisters' playdate is interrupted by two arguing rock giant brothers.

4590.title: Bubble Guppies
4590.description: Meet Monty - the loneliest (and only-est) rhinoceros in the zoo. He needs a friend, and Gil and the Bubble Guppies are determined to help while learning all about habitats at the zoo!

4591.title: Bubble Guppies
4591.description: Once upon a time, Molly and Gil went up a hill to fetch a pail of water. But when a mean Witch, played by Wanda Sykes, turns Bubble Puppy into a frog, Molly and Gil enlist the help of some famous fairytale friends to undo her mean green spell.

4592.title: Dora the Explorer
4592.description: Benny the Bull needs some Sticky Tape in a hurry. His hot air balloon is leaking, and floating toward Crocodile Lake! Dora and Boots rush off to rescue their friend.

4593.title: Dora the Explorer
4593.description: Boots buys a super blue bouncy ball at the store, but it bounces off down the hill.

4594.title: Rusty Rivets
4594.description: Super stinky weeds invade town but Botasaur thinks they're delicious! // Rusty turns Botasaur into the ultimate beach day gadget, but Rusty can't get to the beach to play with him because they keep stopping to help friends in need.

4595.title: Rusty Rivets
4595.description: Mr. Higgins wants to go to the town dance, but thinks he's a terrible dancer. So Rusty and Ruby build a suit that dances for him. // Rusty accidentally causes bees to abandon their hive in the Recycling Yard and must lure them back home.

4596.title: Blaze And The Monster Machines
4596.description: When Blaze and Starla encounter a herd of cows wandering out in the desert, they must embark on a wild west adventure to bring them back to Starla’s barn.

4597.title: Blaze And The Monster Machines
4597.description: It's the day of the Dragon Island Duel, a race around tropical Dragon Island! But when Crusher cheats and sends Blaze away before the race, AJ must set out to rescue his best friend and bring him back to the starting line.

4598.title: PAW Patrol
4598.description: Ryder gets a call from the Circus ringmaster – Ellie the baby elephant has escaped from the circus train! // Mayor Goodway’s purse chicken “Chickaletta” has gone missing. Ryder and the Paw Patrol search Adventure bay.

4599.title: PAW Patrol
4599.description: Ryder and the PAW Patrol have to rescue Alex when he takes off on his new “super trike”. // Marshall proves he is a true hero when he stops to put out a real fire on the beach during a race against the clock for a trophy.

4600.title: PAW Patrol
4600.description: Mr. Porters van full of puppy food slides on the ice near the shore; Ryder and the PAW Patrol must save the day! // Katie and her cat Cali are on the chair lift when it stops leaving them above the ski hill with no way to get down!

4601.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4601.description: Squidward sculpts a statue of Mr. Krabs for The Krusty Krab. // Giant sea whelks terrorize the folks of Bikini Bottom.

4602.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4602.description: SpongeBob and Patrick take a friendship test. // Pearl is embarrassed when she must sit next to SpongeBob in the Tunnel of Glove.

4603.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4603.description: Mr. Krabs decides to start selling hot dogs instead of Krabby Patties. // SpongeBob and Patrick discover a lost ship.

4604.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4604.description: Private's quirky Uncle Nigel pops in for a quick visit from across the pond. // The boys intercept a fax with cartographic news; Maurice has only 24 hours to live. In order to make Maurice's assumed final day comfortable, the entire zoo bands together.

4605.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4605.description: Private discovers a stack of lost comic books. Skipper immediately commands their destruction, citing their risky influence. // Shakespeare in the park has inspired Private as he struts around the zoo spouting iambic pentameter laden insults.

4606.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4606.description: After dealing Taotie yet another humiliating defeat, Po is horrified to learn that the villainous warthog has had a full on nervous breakdown. Po is determined to heal his spirit and Taotie is eager to change his evil ways...or is he?

4607.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4607.description: When Po's fake love letter prank on Monkey backfires, the duo's relationship is put to the test in a story of jealousy, betrayal and, yes, even kidnapping.

4608.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
4608.description: Raph is worried about Casey's ability to handle big mutant threats...when they meet Slash again and discover he has a partner of his own: THE NEWTRALIZER!

4609.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
4609.description: Tiger Claw returns and intends to destroy the Turtles at any cost.

4610.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4610.description: A concert promoter wants to send SpongeBob and Squidward on the road, until greedy Mr. Krabs decides to manage them—and their “world tour”—himself.

4611.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4611.description: SpongeBob's favorite jellyfishing net is missing! And worst of all, Pat may have been the one that stole it. // Rejected yet again by Squidward, SpongeBob decides that if he can't hang with the real Squid, he'll make his own. So SpongeBob builds a ventriloquist dummy modeled after his favorite neighbor.

4612.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4612.description: In an attempt to get away from SpongeBob, Squidward drives off in his boat as fast as he can, but he is pulled over and ordered to go to boating school. // Mr. Krabs decides to go into the tabloid business.

4613.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4613.description: When Temutai kidnaps a kung fu master, Shifu turns to Po for help.

4614.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4614.description: Po discovers his dad, Mr. Ping, is dating Scorpion, but he has trouble trusting his former enemy who claims to no longer be evil.

4615.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4615.description: The penguins discover the abuse that Randy the sheep gets in the children's zoo from all the children with sticky hands tugging at his wool, and decide to find him a new home. // The duckling Eggy is back. The training that the penguins gave him worked.

4616.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4616.description: The penguins are on a mission to fulfill wishes. Private tells Mort that if he throws a penny in the fountain his wish will come true. // King Julien has just discovered April Fools Day. Making up for lost time, he terrorizes the zoo with pranks.

4617.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
4617.description: When the Rat King returns, Splinter must overcome his guilt and fear of the Rat King controlling his mind in order to defeat his foe once and for all.

4618.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
4618.description: Facing Shredder's deadly new assassin, Leo must decide whether to risk his brother's lives or ask for Splinter's help. Donnie must put aside his rivalry with Casey in order to uncover a new Kraang plot.

4619.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4619.description: Mr. Krabs and Plankton have been business rivals and bitter enemies for longer than anyone can remember. But one day, Mr. Krabs reveals that they were not always this way. There was a time when the two rivals were best friends.

4620.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4620.description: Mr. Krab's old fry cook pays a special visit to the Krusty Krab. SpongeBob is in awe of his predecessor, who has since become a world renowned chef following his departure from Krabs' restaurant. // Tales of the boogeyman sends SpongeBob into panic. Every dark corner in his house could be a potential hiding place for the infamous monster.

4621.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4621.description: SpongeBob finds a nasty sea urchin living in the Krusty Krab, and tries everything to force it out. // After getting his groceries stolen, Squidward convinces SpongeBob and Sandy to teach him karate.

4622.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4622.description: Po realizes he must select a trophy for the Hall of Heroes, but instead finds himself helping a young villager retrieve a rabbit doll that is much more important than it looks.

4623.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4623.description: Po disguises himself as the merciless villain, Tong Fo, to try and locate a hidden weapon.

4624.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4624.description: The toy manufacturer of Rico's doll-girlfriend has upgraded their doll line with a voice chip. // When the penguins are photographed while in action and placed on the new zoo poster they have to stop the presses before the poster gets out to the public.

4625.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4625.description: King Julien observes children chasing each other, calling out "cooties". He deduces that girls pass this wretched "cooties" with a simple touch. // When Rico crashes the Penguins car and rebuilds it himself, it becomes "possessed" and targets Rico.

4626.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
4626.description: On the eve of the eclipse, Aang's anxiety gets the better of him. His dreams become nightmares, and soon he can no longer tell dream from reality.

4627.title: Avatar: The Last Airbender
4627.description: It is the Day of Black Sun and the group meets up with the invasion force."The day has finally arrived and Aang is ready to take on the Fire Lord. But they soon realize that things aren't going to go according to plan, and their surprise attack isn't so unexpected." Part 2 is "The Day of Black Sun, Part 2: The Eclipse."

4628.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4628.description: Determined to uncover Plankton’s next devious plot, Mr. Krabs sends SpongeBob and Patrick to spy on him. // Watch an instructional video on boating techniques with Squidward and SpongeBob. // Mr. Krabs holds a contest for his employees: The first one to learn the names of every Krusty Krab customer wins a tropical vacation.

4629.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4629.description: After arriving one minute late for work, SpongeBob decides to move into the Krusty Krab so that he will never be late to work again. // When Plankton secretly turns down the thermostat at the Krusty Krab the entire restaurant freezes over. But with a couple of frozen Krabby Patties tied to his shoes for skates, SpongeBob turns the frozen floor into an ice rink

4630.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4630.description: The scariest roller coaster ever has just opened at Bikini Bottom's amusement park. At first SpongeBob and Patrick are determined to ride it, but the more they think about how scary it is the more they chicken out. // Plankton tricks SpongeBob, Patrick and Squidward into fixing up the Chum Bucket.

4631.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
4631.description: Facing Shredder's deadly new assassin, Leo must decide whether to risk his brother's lives or ask for Splinter's help. Donnie must put aside his rivalry with Casey in order to uncover a new Kraang plot.

4632.title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
4632.description: The Turtles try to relax by playing a fantasy role-playing game, but when the game becomes real, they must learn the difference between fantasy and reality.

4633.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4633.description: When Taotie tries to destroy the Jade Palace and fails, he is sent to prison while his son, Bian Zao, is left behind with Po, who acts like a big brother to the boy who thinks everything is lame!

4634.title: Kung Fu Panda: Legends of Awesomeness
4634.description: While repairs are being made to the noodle shop, Mr. Ping turns the training hall into a restaurant!

4635.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4635.description: The Amarillo Kid confronts the penguins looking for the infamous Mr. Tux. Apparently the two have a score to settle. // Private is ready to move up in rank within the penguin commando unit, or is he? First he'll have to become a First Class Private.

4636.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4636.description: Kowalski is near completion with his mind reading device. But where can he find a processor? // The zoo's new badger exhibit has Private terrified. Marlene sets out to calm his panic by introducing him to the new zoo neighbors, Becky and Stacy.

4637.title: The Penguins of Madagascar
4637.description: Due to the high rate of gadget malfunction, Skipper orders Kowalski to cease with the science. But Kowalski can't resist, he must invent. // When a baby's stroller rolls outside the zoo the penguins chase the baby through the streets of New York.

4638.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4638.description: SpongeBob has trouble saying Goodbye to the most perfect Krabby Patty he has ever cooked up. // After electrocuting himself on his own security fence, Squidward’s personality gets completely scrambled. Now he is the most jovial Squid to ever live in Bikini Bottom – and he’s starting to get on everyone’s nerves.

4639.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4639.description: Mr. Krabs makes a wish that he could talk to money. When his wish is magically granted, Krabs learns (to his horror) what all of his dollars, pennies and quarters have been longing for: they want Krabs to spend them. // Squidward trains SpongeBob for the Bikini Bottom dance contest.

4640.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
4640.description: SpongeBob becomes the latest local obsession after a notable food critic gives him high ratings. Now Mr. Krabs is looking to cash in on the fad by making everything in the Krusty Krab Sponge-themed. // SpongeBob helps Patrick get his song some air time at the local radio station.
